title: FreightTrain Quarterly Fall 2008 v03i03
description:
Welcome in Steve Jones as the designer. He&#039;s much better at it than me. It should mean this issue looks better and is easier to read. You can find out more about him at sgj-design.com.

He also drew two awesome sketches that you&#039;ll find in the magazine. Send him a nice note at his website and maybe he&#039;ll draw you a picture too.

We only have two stories in this issue, but they are both really good. "In the Kitchen, After the War" by Adam Moorad and "When Maggie Went Away" by Tammy L. Remington.
